      "text": "Altostrat Singapore provides eligible employees and interns with up to 14 days of paid outpatient sick leave per calendar year, compensated at 100% of their base salary. For part-time and fixed-term employees, this leave is prorated based on their contracted working hours.\n\nYou must notify your manager at least one hour before your normal start time if you need to take sick leave. If your manager is unavailable, you must contact support.\n\nIf you are sick for more than two work days, you must submit a sick certificate from a registered medical practitioner via WorkWeek within 48 hours of taking the leave. Failure to submit the Medical Certificate (MC) may result in the company declining paid sick leave, classifying the absence as unpaid, and potentially leading to disciplinary action.\n\n**Section 1.1 Outpatient Sick Time & Hospitalization Leave (Singapore)**\n**Section 19.2 Outpatient Sick Leave**"
    }
  ],
  "role": "model"
}

